\sum^{i=n}_{i=0} \left(-\frac{2}{3}\right)^i
|r|<1
S=\displaystyle\sum_{i=0}^n r
rS=r+r^2+\ldots+r^{n+1}
rS-S=r^{n+1}-1
|r|<1
\lim_{n\to\infty}r^{n+1}=0
\frac{1}{1-r}
r=-\frac{2}{3}
\frac{1}{1+\frac{2}.{3}}=\frac{3}{5}
S=\frac{1-r^{n+1}}{1-r}.
\sum^{i=n}_{i=0} \left(-\frac{2}{3}\right)^i = \frac 3 5
\lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{1-(-2/3)^{n+1}}{5/3}= \frac 3 5
